I&#39;ve been investigating how to create a synchronization pipe that will get updated data from several sources and update several targets based on type of the source data. Lets say I have two sources, the first one will provide me with updated `Customers` and `Products` the other one will provide `Customers` and `Purchases`. On the other side I currently have two targets one should be updated with `Customers` data the other one with `Products`. Obviously at some point I&#39;ll have another target and maybe additional sources.
So I decided to build a service that will be the central pipe which will load the plugins, created and assembly with `IDataSource` and `IHandler` like the following:

    public interface IDataSource
    {
        string Name { get; }
        List&lt;T&gt; Execute&lt;T&gt;(object context);
        List&lt;Type&gt; Initialize();
    }
    public interface IHandler
    {
        string Name { get; }
        void Execute&lt;T&gt;(object context, List&lt;T&gt; data);
        List&lt;Type&gt; Initialize();
    }
The same assembly also contains definitions for `CustomerDTO`,`ProductDTO` and `PurchaseDTO`, the idea is that the pipe will load and instantiate the plugins, get the supported entity types by each of the plugins using the `Initialize` method, and then for each source request the data one entity type at a time:

            var handlerDefs = new Dictionary&lt;Type, List&lt;IHandler&gt;&gt;();
            foreach (var handler in PluginLoader&lt;IHandler&gt;.LoadPlugins(&quot;plugins&quot;))
            {
                foreach (var type in handler.Initialize())
